definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.

An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.

A glycolipid that consists of an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which both acyl groups have a chain length of C12 or greater.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 18 carbons and 1 double bond.

An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer(d16:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.

A glycolipid that consists of an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 2-monoacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which the acyl group has a chain length of C12 or greater.
A C-glycosyl compound that is apigenin substituted by beta-D-glucopyranosyl and an alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl moieties at positions 6 and 8 via C-glycosidic linkages.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 22 carbons and 6 double bonds.

An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1)-Cer(d20:1) arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 22 carbons and 4 double bonds.
An L-isoleucine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-isoleucine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.
A galactoglycerolipid that consists of a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3 of a 2-monoacyl-sn-glycerol moiety in which the acyl group has a chain length of C12 or greater.
An L-leucine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-leucine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.
A beta-D-galactopyranosyl diglyceride in which both acyl groups have a chain length of C12 or greater.
An L-lysine derivative that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-lysine with the amino group of 2-naphthylamine.

A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative in which two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl pentasaccharide chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end.
A 3-(beta-D-galactosyl)monooctanoyl-sn-glycerol in which the octanoyl group is located at position 2.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and hexadecanoyl respectively.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkenyl and acyl groups are specified asas (1Z)-octadecenyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.

A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoyl respectively.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z,11Z)-octadecadienyl and linoleoyl respectively.

A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl and the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (1Z,9Z)-octadecadienyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which one acyl group has 16 carbons and 1 double bond while the other has 18 carbons and is fully saturated.
A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which one acyl group has 18 carbons and is fully saturated while the other has 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A phosphatidyl-L-serine in which both acyl groups have 20 carbons and 4 double bonds.
An N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as nonadecanoyl.
A glycoglycerolipid that consists of 3-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl]-sn-glycerol in which the glycerol portion is acylated at position 2 by an octanoyl group.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as (11Z)-icosenoyl.
An alpha-NeuNAc-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-NeuNAc-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as henicosanoyl.

An alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tetracosanoyl.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as octadecanoyl.
A hexadecatrienoate that is the conjugate base of (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A biflavonoid that is a 7, 4', 4'''-trimethyl ether derivative of amentoflavone.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphinganine in which the acyl group is specified as (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.

An anionic ganglioside arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer; major species at pH 7.3.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a nonadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear octasaccharide units.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an nonadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear octasaccharide units.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a pentadecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked linked (1->3) and (1->6) two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear hexasaccharide units.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are both linoleoyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl).
